        <question><text>If Earth used to shrink to half its radius with mass constant, day duration?</text><option id="A">6 hours</option><option id="B">12 hours</option><option id="C">48 hours</option><option id="D">24 hours</option><answer>A</answer><explanation>L const. I1w1 = I2w2. (2/5 MR^2) 2pi/T = (2/5 M (R/2)^2) 2pi/T'. R^2/T = (R^2/4)/T'. T' = T/4 = 24/4 = 6h.</explanation></question>
