        <question><text>Work done to move a body of mass m from surface of Earth (R) to height h=R?</text><option id="A">mgR/2</option><option id="B">mgR</option><option id="C">2mgR</option><option id="D">mgR/4</option><answer>A</answer><explanation>Delta U = -GMm(1/(R+R) - 1/R) = -GMm(-1/2R) = GMm/2R. g = GM/R^2 => GM/R = gR. Delta U = mgR/2.</explanation></question>
        <question><text>Three particles of mass M at corners of equilateral triangle side L. Speed to move in circle maintaining separation?</text><option id="A">sqrt(GM/L)</option><option id="B">sqrt(3GM/L)</option><option id="C">sqrt(GM/L(sqrt(3)))</option><option id="D">Zero</option><answer>A</answer><explanation>F_net towards center = 2 * F * cos 30 = 2 * (GM^2/L^2) * sqrt(3)/2 = sqrt(3) GM^2/L^2. Centripetal = M v^2 / r. r = L/sqrt(3). sqrt(3) GM^2/L^2 = M v^2 / (L/sqrt(3)). 3 GM / L^2 = v^2 / (L). 3 GM / L = v^2? Wait. Force towards center. F_net = sqrt(3)F. r = L/sqrt(3). Mv^2/r = F_net. Mv^2 * sqrt(3)/L = sqrt(3) GM^2/L^2. v^2 = GM/L. v = sqrt(GM/L).</explanation></question>
