        <question><text>Mass M is split into m and (M-m). For max force between them, m/M is:</text><option id="A">1/2</option><option id="B">1/4</option><option id="C">1/3</option><option id="D">1</option><answer>A</answer><explanation>d/dm (m(M-m)) = M-2m = 0. m = M/2.</explanation></question>
        <question><text>A body weighs 63N on surface. Weight at height R/2?</text><option id="A">28 N</option><option id="B">31.5 N</option><option id="C">42 N</option><option id="D">63 N</option><answer>A</answer><explanation>g' = g (R/(R+0.5R))^2 = g (1/1.5)^2 = g (2/3)^2 = 4/9 g. W' = 4/9 * 63 = 4 * 7 = 28N.</explanation></question>
        <question><text>Orbital speed of a satellite depends on:</text><option id="A">Mass of planet and Radius of orbit</option><option id="B">Mass of satellite</option><option id="C">Orbit shape</option><option id="D">Rocket fuel</option><answer>A</answer><explanation>sqrt(GM/r).</explanation></question>
