        <question>
            <text>The gravitational field in a region is E = (2i + 3j) N/kg. Work done to move 1kg from (0,0) to (2,1)?</text>
            <option id="A">-7 J</option>
            <option id="B">7 J</option><option id="C">5 J</option><option id="D">-5 J</option>
            <answer>A</answer>
            <explanation>W_ext = - W_field. F_field = mE. W_field = F.d = (2i+3j).(2i+j) = 4+3=7. W_ext = -7 (against field). BUT Potential diff V_f - V_i = - Int E.dr. Delta U = m Delta V. If we move against field, we do +work? Work done "by field" is 7J. Work done "to move" usually implies external agent, which is -7J. Wait. Force on particle is F. To move it, we apply -F. Work = (-F).d = -(7) = -7J. Correct.</explanation>
        </question>
