        <question><text>A solid sphere of mass M radius R has a point mass m at center. Work to move m to infinity?</text><option id="A">GMm/R</option><option id="B">GMm/2R</option><option id="C">3GMm/2R</option><option id="D">Integrated</option><answer>C</answer><explanation>Potential at center of solid sphere is -1.5 GM/R. Work = 0 - m(-1.5 GM/R) = 1.5 GMm/R.</explanation></question>
        <!-- Adding more hard questions -->
        <question><text>Maximum height reached by a rocket fired with velocity v = 0.9 ve?</text><option id="A">R (approx 4R)</option><option id="B">9R</option><option id="C">R/(1-0.81)</option><option id="D">10R</option><answer>A</answer><explanation>-GMm/R + 1/2 m (0.9 ve)^2 = -GMm/(R+h). ve^2 = 2GM/R. -GM/R + 0.81 GM/R = -GM/(R+h). -0.19/R = -1/(R+h). R+h = R/0.19 = 5.26R. h = 4.26R.</explanation></question>
        <question><text>A satellite in equatorial plane has period T. Earth rotates with T0. Apparent period as seen from Earth (same sense)?</text><option id="A">1 / (1/T - 1/T0)</option><option id="B">T + T0</option><option id="C">sqrt(TT0)</option><option id="D">Zero</option><answer>A</answer><explanation>w_rel = w - w0. 2pi/T_app = 2pi/T - 2pi/T0.</explanation></question>
        <question><text>Three stars mass M at equilateral triangle rotating. Radius R circumcircle. Period?</text><option id="A">2pi sqrt(R^3/3GM)</option><option id="B">2pi sqrt(R^3/GM)</option><option id="C">Formula</option><option id="D">Skip</option><answer>A</answer><explanation>F = sqrt(3) GM^2/L^2. L = sqrt(3)R. F = sqrt(3) GM^2 / 3R^2 = GM^2 / sqrt(3)R^2. Fc = M w^2 R. w^2 = GM / sqrt(3) R^3. T = 2pi R^1.5 / sqrt(GM/sqrt(3)).</explanation></question>
        <question><text>A planet moves in ellipse. r_min and r_max given. Relation between v_min and v_max?</text><option id="A">v1 r1 = v2 r2</option><option id="B">Energy eq</option><option id="C">v1/r1 = v2/r2</option><option id="D">None</option><answer>A</answer><explanation>Angular momentum conservation.</explanation></question>
