        <question><text>Infinite number of masses m, 2m, 4m, 8m... at r, 2r, 4r, 8r... Potential at origin?</text><option id="A">-4Gm/3r</option><option id="B">Infinite</option><option id="C">-2Gm/r</option><option id="D">Zero</option><answer>A</answer><explanation>Sum = -G(m/r + 2m/2r + 4m/4r ...) = -Gm/r (1+1+1...)? Diverges. Bad question setup. Series: m/r, m/2r, m/4r etc? If m kept at 1, 2, 4, 8: m/1 + m/2 + m/4... Geometric series 1/(1-0.5) = 2. Total -2Gm/r. Question text needs fix: "Masses m placed at r, 2r, 4r, 8r..." Option C fits well.</explanation></question>
        <question><text>Distance of null point between Earth (M) and Moon (M/81) where D is distance?</text><option id="A">0.9 D</option><option id="B">0.1 D</option><option id="C">0.5 D</option><option id="D">0.81 D</option><answer>A</answer><explanation>sqrt(M)/x = sqrt(m)/(D-x). 1/x = (1/9)/(D-x). 9(D-x) = x. 9D = 10x. x=0.9D.</explanation></question>
        <question><text>A satellite loses energy due to drag. Effect?</text><option id="A">Radius decreases, Speed increases</option><option id="B">Radius increases, Speed decreases</option><option id="C">Both decrease</option><option id="D">Stops</option><answer>A</answer><explanation>Drops to lower orbit, paradox of satellites (speeds up due to lower PE).</explanation></question>
